---
description: Voice call infrastructure rules — Twilio, Whisper STT, recording, S3
globs: backend/app/services/twilio_service.py, backend/app/services/transcription_service.py, backend/app/services/storage_service.py, backend/app/realtime/call_stream_handler.py, backend/app/api/v1/twilio_webhooks.py, backend/app/api/v1/calls.py, frontend/src/lib/twilio.ts, frontend/src/hooks/use-call.ts
---

Call infrastructure stack:
- Twilio Voice SDK (outbound/inbound calls, capability tokens, TwiML)
- Twilio Media Streams (real-time raw audio via WebSocket → backend)
- OpenAI Whisper API (`whisper-1`) for speech-to-text
- AWS S3 (call recording storage, presigned URLs for playback)
- Audio format utilities: mulaw → PCM16 WAV conversion (`app/utils/audio.py`)

Backend voice rules:
- All Twilio SDK operations must be isolated in `app/services/twilio_service.py` — no direct Twilio calls elsewhere.
- All S3 operations must be isolated in `app/services/storage_service.py`.
- All Whisper/STT operations must be isolated in `app/services/transcription_service.py`.
- Twilio webhook handlers (`app/api/v1/twilio_webhooks.py`) must validate Twilio request signatures before processing.
- Call state transitions (initiated → ringing → in_progress → completed/failed) must be recorded in the `calls` table via status callbacks.
- Recording URLs from Twilio recording callbacks must be stored in the `calls.recording_url` column.
- Batch transcription (post-call) must run as a Celery task — never block the webhook HTTP response.
- Real-time audio streaming: Twilio Media Stream delivers mulaw-encoded audio over WebSocket → convert to WAV chunks in `app/realtime/call_stream_handler.py` → forward to Whisper for live STT.
- Speaker diarization (agent vs. customer) must be applied and stored in `call_transcripts.speaker`.
- All transcripts must be stored per-utterance in the `call_transcripts` table with `start_time`, `end_time`, `confidence`, and `speaker`.

Recording and storage rules:
- All recordings must be stored in S3; never serve raw Twilio recording URLs to clients.
- Use presigned S3 URLs (short TTL, e.g. 1 hour) for client playback — generated by `StorageService.get_presigned_url()`.
- Recordings contain PII (call audio); follow data retention and access control requirements.
- Do not store unencrypted recordings in publicly accessible S3 buckets; use bucket policies + signed URLs.

Frontend Twilio rules:
- Twilio Device initialization must be in `lib/twilio.ts` — consumed via `hooks/use-call.ts`.
- Capability tokens must be fetched from `GET /api/v1/calls/token` — never generated client-side.
- Call state machine (idle → calling → connected → ended) must be managed in Zustand `call-store.ts`.
- Call controls (mute, hold, end, transfer) must reflect actual Twilio Device state; do not allow UI-only state mismatch.
- Never expose Twilio Account SID, Auth Token, or API secrets to the frontend.

Latency and performance:
- Audio chunk size for real-time transcription: target 250ms–500ms chunks to balance latency vs. accuracy.
- Real-time STT → analysis → guidance round-trip target: < 2 seconds end-to-end.
- Use async I/O and Redis pub/sub to avoid blocking the WebSocket handler during Whisper calls.

Do not:
- Call Twilio APIs directly from route handlers — always go through `TwilioService`.
- Store raw audio in PostgreSQL — always use S3.
- Block the Twilio webhook HTTP response with long-running AI tasks — dispatch to Celery.
- Hardcode Twilio credentials; use `app/config.py` + env vars.
- Mix voice-specific logic with chat or generic conversation logic.
